SIMPLE: namely
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Namely
<hw>Name"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>By name; by
particular mention; specifically; especially; expressly.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The solitariness of man . . . God hath <qex>namely</qex> and
principally ordered to prevent by marriage.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That is to say; to wit; videlicet; -- introducing a
particular or specific designation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For the excellency of the soul, <qex>namely</qex>, its power of
divining dreams; that several such divinations have been made, none can
question.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Namer</ent>⟦br⟧
